<br>
28-32 extra imbue points available. Probably 32, because shields are so cheap. Load it up with resistances for when you are getting hit. Possibly even over-charge it, once again - shields are cheap.<br>
<br>
A charge on your shield.<br>
<br>
Possibly you might confuse the enemy into thinking you are a healer or shaman - saving any real healer or shaman in your group. Especially if you carry a hammer like I do.<br>
<br>
You can still switch to 2-hander when bashing an enemy and not getting hit.<br>
<br>
What does everyone think? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nattfari>Nattfari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/26/02 2:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 2h &gt; 1h imo</span><hr size=1> As I recently acquired the 1h legion Blade of Power I tried going 1h and shiled for a couple of days last week.  I didnt really like it and have returned to my usual 2h.  Hardly blocked at all, was using a 100% quality lvl 51 shield, and it felt like it took longer to kill peeps.  Didnt do any solid testing, was just how it felt.<br>
<br>
<br>
Nattfari Eldibrandur<br>
Elding Herra of &lt;Nothing&gt;<br>
Pellinor <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=irken>Irken</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/26/02 2:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 2h &gt; 1h imo</span><hr size=1> I imbued a 99qua Duskwood Reinforced Round shield with 7thrust, 7 slash, 7 body resists, and 52 hits.  Not too shabby.  Also got a 99qua Arc Dwarven Short sword that I put 5 sword 5Parry on.  Makes a decent combo.  Just waiting to get a nice qua Arc Dwarven Great Sword to imbue.  I have Matter Based DOT procs on all my weapons and a sweet Haste Charge on my cloak now.  Makes for a nice couple of SC'd items....<br>
<br>
Is it worth it to switch between 1hr and 2hr just for the bonus' on the shield.  Maybe not, but it's an option if you need the resists or not.<br>
<br>
/shrug <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gisborne>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 190<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/26/02 2:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 2h &gt; 1h imo</span><hr size=1> Hmm....look at it like this. Even if you could imbue your shield with +7 resist to everything (way way way beyond what you really could do) that would mean you'd take 7% less damage. You'd block maybe 3-5% of the total damage you'd take (melee and spell) if you had really high dex. So in a best case scenario you'd take 10-12% less damage. On the other hand, you'd do 25% less melee damage on average (even less if you take front-loading into account). Even if we generously assume that only half your damage output is from melee (the other half DD's) you'd still gain 12.5% from using a 2H.<br>
<br>
In other words, even if we stretched the limits of possibility, 2H is better than 1H.<br>
<br>
 <p>Eka, lvl 49 skald Percival</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grigrock>GrigRock</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/26/02 4:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 1hander works</span><hr size=1> I'm a 50 skald and have been for sometime now. I recently decided just for fun to see what it would be like to go 1hander for a while. My main concern in RvR is casters and Skalds make excellent caster killers but with a slow 2h a caster can get off a stun/mez/root before your next swing. I got tired of running up to a caster swinging and missing due to BT and then standing around for up 5.4 secs. I find that I can keep up to 3 casters busy with a quick weapon switching targets and annoying them. I'm not a glory hound I just keep them busy long enough for our own casters to own them. I do switch between 1h and 2h but it's a lot of work to do so. Oh and increase your Dex! I block and parry twice as much since SC has allowed me to buff my dex to max.<br>
Thanks,<br>
Roch E<br>
&lt;Shield Maidens&gt;<br>
50 Skald Palomides<br>
