<br>
With a 2H 98% Arc War Cleaver, The fight wasnt really close..<br>
<br>
With the 1H I believe I was using Varulbane (best 1H I had on me at the time), all the fights were very close.<br>
<br>
Two reasons for that.<br>
1. Evade will kill you when using a 2H'r. You get Evaded twice and you are absolutely done for.<br>
<br>
2. Stun. Stun. Stun. Stun absolutely changes things and Skalds rarely get to Stun. I am a Axe user and my only stun is a med stun of a parry which I am trying to up and use SC'ing for added Dex. I am less then 10 dex from the cap so I now have a very high dex and with about 31 parry If I remember correct, I am seeing a increase in parry. With a 1H I have a better chance to parry. Well not actually to parry but to counter if I do parry. If I am using a 2H and I parry and he hits me before I swing that slower 2H then I lose my comeback. One fight I got the comeback in and only a couple evades and the fight wasnt really that close. <br>
<br>
Now I now this is against a rogue class but I would go with a 1H against a caster also. So that means 1h for caster and for rogue classes. 2H for tanks? Well good luck against any true melee's now anyway with all the changes. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
